news.title: Apco Infratech buys 9,527 sq ft apartment in Pali Hill from Ashar Group for Rs 172 crore
news.para: This transaction was achieved at the rate of Rs 1.81 lakh per sq ft and the buyer has paid a stamp duty of Rs 9.30 crore.

news.title: NPKL allottees slam Bengaluru development body's decision to collect road-cutting fee
news.para: The Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout Open Forum wrote a letter to the Chief Minister on May 14, 2024, directing the BDA not to collect Rs 31,000 from the site owners.

news.title: The land ownership conundrum in village of South Delhi
news.para: Lal Dora was used in the past to demarcate the jurisdiction of a village on land where the population resided. When the population increased and villagers got a plot for a house against their scattered agricultural land holdings under the ‘chakbandi’ scheme, the concept of extended Lal Dora was introduced.

news.title: Housing board buildings unsafe, need urgent help: Goa legislators
news.para: Speaking during a calling attention motion in the assembly, they said these buildings are in a very fragile state, with families still residing in them. The MLAs called on govt to take action before any untoward incident occurs.

news.title: Goa's cabinet approve bill to take over land with no owners
news.para: The proposal also seeks to introduce a comprehensive legislative framework to govern the manegement of specific types of property that become vested in state govt.

news.title: Registration to be must for installing lifts & escalators in buildings in Bihar
news.para: The Bihar Lift and Escalator Bill, 2024 was tabled in the House by Energy Minister Bijendra Prasad Yadav and was passed by voice vote after the opposition staged a walkout.

news.title: Over 4,200 homes registered in Kolkata in June to avail stamp duty rebate
news.para: ​The state govt had announced the withdrawal of the incentives — including 2% stamp duty rebate and 10% reduction in circle rate — effective from July 1, 2024.

news.title: Kerala government to reduce building permit fees
news.para: The new rate would reduce the permit fee by at least 50 per cent for houses with an area from 81 square metres to 300 square metres, Local Self-Government Department (LSGD) Minister M B Rajesh said here.

news.title: CCI dismisses complaint against Indiabulls Housing Finance, 19 others
news.para: Dismissing the complaint, the regulator in an order on Monday said, "the Commission is of the view that prima facie there is no competition concern arising in the present matter under the provisions of Section 3 and Section 4 of the Act and therefore, the matter is directed to be closed forthwith".

news.title: Otis cuts annual sales view on slowdown in construction activity in China, US
news.para: The company expects its full-year net sales to be between $14.3 billion and $14.5 billion, down from its previous forecast of $14.5 billion to $14.8 billion.

news.title: Home sales in USA dip 5.4% in June 2024
news.para: Sales of previously occupied U.S. homes fell 5.4% last month from May to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 3.89 million, the fourth consecutive month of declines, the National Association of Realtors said Tuesday.

news.title: Deutsche Bank says commercial real estate remains under pressure
news.para: Chief financial officer James von Moltke told journalists that conditions were improving but more slowly than he had anticipated and provisions for commercial real estate in the U.S. will continue to be impacted.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace Developers reports profit of Rs 12.74 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Its total income increased to Rs 206.70 crore during the April-June period of this fiscal year from Rs 110.05 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding financial year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Karnataka government tabled bill to levy property tax on unauthorised buildings
news.para: The municipalities Bill, tabled by urban development minister BS Suresh (Byrathi), seeks to fine officials up to Rs 50,000 and imprison them for 15 days if they fail to collect property tax dues.

news.title: E-khata integration to combat illegal registration of land in Karnataka
news.para: Byre Gowda was replying in the assembly to allegations by BJP’s SR Vishwanath, who accused sub-registrars of colluding with land sharks to illegally register agricultural land as residential and commercial plots.

news.title: Kajaria Ceramics' net profit dips 15.39% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Kajaria Ceramics' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,123.88 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 4.69 per cent from Rs 1,073.49 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP issues show-cause notices to 100 homes over illegal construction
news.para: Despite these notices, no satisfactory response has been received from any house owner, prompting the department to prepare restoration orders, said DTCP officials.

news.title: Sale of property of Rs 50 lakh or more involving multiple sellers, buyers to attract TDS
news.para: The government on Tuesday said that one per cent TDS will be applicable for transfer of immovable property involving multiple sellers or buyers wherein the aggregate consideration is Rs 50 lakh or more.
